    "THE JACKSON ADVOCATE 1252 N Farfsh StreelPhone 21617 Publaiivd Weekly at Jackson Mississippi Entered as secondclass matter in Post Office at Jackson Mtw July 13 1945 under Act of Congress March 13 1879 PERCY GREENE Editor and General Manager SUBSCRIPTION RATES All Subscriptions Due and Payable in Advance Single Copy 6c One Year 350 6 Months 200 3 Months 125 I Make all checks payable to The Jackson Advocate In all things that are purely social we can be as separate as the fingers but in all things that affect our mutual progress and de velopment we can be together as the handBooker T Washington Violence Terrorism And Hate In the news about Mississippi dealing with the renewed and growing effort on the part of its Negro citizens to gain the right to vote as all other citizens of the state both published and unpub lished there is much evidence of resort to violence terrorism and suppression by those who would continually deny them that right The newly developed interest on the part of Negro citizens of Mis sissippi in winning the right to vote will never die It can be suppressed But to suppress it there must be a"
